      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how exhausting it is to feel like your life is just a loop of grief with no end in sight. It makes sense that you feel empty and disconnected when the world feels so quiet without them, but please know that this numbness is a sign of how deep your love is, not a sign that you're broken. You don't have to push through the pain alone; reaching out to a crisis line or a therapist can offer a safe space to talk about this crushing weight without judgment.",
